Third-party components
======================

libsepol 3.10 (SELinux userspace), LGPL-2.1, statically linked under the
authoritative-categorizer feature.

  - Used only when RuleSteward is built with the optional
    `authoritative-categorizer` Cargo feature. The default build links no
    libsepol and carries no LGPL obligation.
  - Built from the libsepol 3.10 source vendored in-tree at
    crates/rulesteward-selinux-sys/vendor/libsepol/ and statically linked
    (the build recipe + version pin are in that directory's README.txt; the
    build is driven by crates/rulesteward-selinux-sys/build.rs).
  - License: GNU Lesser General Public License, version 2.1. The full text is
    in LICENSES/LGPL-2.1.txt and in vendor/libsepol/LICENSE. The complete,
    corresponding libsepol source is included in this repository under
    crates/rulesteward-selinux-sys/vendor/libsepol/ (upstream:
    https://github.com/SELinuxProject/selinux, release 3.10), satisfying the
    LGPL-2.1 source-availability requirement for any feature-enabled binary.

The single-static-binary distribution model is preserved: libsepol is linked
into the feature-enabled binary as a static archive (LGPL-2.1 permits static
linking with this notice and the accompanying license text).
